# 🌱 Mycelia Network

> **A personal offline AI ecosystem connecting knowledge, sensors, computer vision, automation, and intelligent devices into one unified local platform.**

---

## 📖 Overview

Mycelia Network is my long-term personal engineering project that explores how multiple independent systems can work together as a single intelligent ecosystem.

Rather than relying on cloud services, Mycelia Network is designed around an **offline-first philosophy**, allowing AI, knowledge management, IoT devices, and automation to operate entirely on a local network.

The project is inspired by the biological **mycelium** found beneath forests—a living network that connects, communicates, and shares resources between organisms.

Instead of trees, Mycelia Network connects software, hardware, and AI.

---

# 🌱 Core Components

## 🧠 Mycelium App

The desktop knowledge graph and Markdown editor.

Features include:

- 📝 Markdown knowledge base
- 🕸️ Interactive knowledge graph
- 🤖 Semantic Search
- 🧠 Sentence Transformer integration
- 💬 Local RAG AI Assistant
- 📚 Synonym learning
- 🔒 Fully offline

---

## 📟 My_Skin

The sensory layer of Mycelia.

Built around an ESP32, My_Skin observes the physical world and streams environmental data into the network.

Current sensors include:

- 🌡️ Temperature
- 💧 Humidity
- ⏰ Date & Time (RTC)
- 📺 LCD Display
- 📡 Wi-Fi communication

---

## 🧠 mybrain

A lightweight local Flask server responsible for receiving, processing, and distributing information between components.

Current responsibilities include:

- 📥 Receiving sensor data
- 💾 Writing Markdown files
- 🤖 Serving AI requests
- 🔗 Connecting applications

---

## 👁️ Vision

Computer vision modules built with Python and OpenCV.

Current capabilities:

- 😀 Face Detection
- 👤 Face Recognition
- 📷 Webcam Integration

---

# ⚙️ Philosophy

Mycelia Network is built on five core principles.

- 🔒 Privacy First
- 🌍 Offline First
- 🧩 Modular Design
- 🧠 AI Assisted
- 🌱 Continuous Growth

Every component should be useful on its own while becoming more powerful when connected to the rest of the ecosystem.

---

# 🔮 Long-Term Vision

My goal is to create a personal AI ecosystem capable of:

- 🧠 Learning from personal knowledge
- 👁️ Understanding the surrounding environment
- 📟 Collecting real-world sensor data
- 🤖 Interacting naturally through conversation
- ⚙️ Automating repetitive tasks
- 🌱 Growing continuously over time

Rather than replacing existing tools, Mycelia Network aims to unify them into a single intelligent platform that remains entirely under the user's control.

